The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in machine learning tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The focus on executing CNN inference on resource-constrained devices suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and augmented reality (cs.AR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of sensor-equipped Internet of Things (IoT) devices could also relate to the embedded systems (cs.EM) sub-category.
